      • effectiveUri

        public Uri effectiveUri(Uri uri,
                        scala.collection.immutable.Seq<HttpHeader> headers,
                        boolean securedConnection,
                        Host defaultHostHeader)
        Determines the effective request URI according to the logic defined at http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7230#section-5.5

        Throws an IllegalUriException if the URI is relative and the headers don't include a valid Host header or if URI authority and Host header don't match.

        Parameters:

        headers - (undocumented)

      • verifyUri

        public void verifyUri(Uri uri)
        Verifies that the given Uri is non-empty and has either scheme http, https, ws, wss or no scheme at all. If any of these conditions is not met the method throws an IllegalUriException.
        Parameters:
